  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 6th level, you have the ability to twist fate using your wild magic. When another creature you can see makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a saving throw, you can use your reaction and spend 2 @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete.5e-class-features.7hAcETWHOVguR2ZF]{Sorcery Points} to roll [[/r 1d4]] and apply the number rolled as a bonus or penalty (your choice) to the creature's roll. You can do so after the creature rolls but before any effects of the roll occur.</p><section id=\"secret-3kefaN6nnMAEDxFT\" class=\"secret\"><p><em>Note: After adding this feature to your character, set Resource Consumption to Item Uses: Font of Magic: 2</em></p></section>",
